    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL RIDE OPTIMIZED SUSPENSION (IROS) - REMOVE AND INSTALL - SUSPENSION AIR SPRINGS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SUSPENSION AIR SPRINGS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal of Suspension Air Springs</title>
            <figure id="f0301216" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg03/G0301216.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Air Spring Location And Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. AXLE STOP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SPRING HANGER CASTING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. LOWER SHOCK ABSORBER MTG BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. MAIN SUPPORT MEMBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. AIR SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. AIR SPRING MTG BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. UPPER SHOCK ABSORBER MTG BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When replacing air springs, use only approved International parts for vehicle.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unload vehicle and block wheels to prevent vehicle from rolling. Support vehicle with
                    floor stands.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0301217" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg03/G0301217.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                             scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 16. Air Spring Mounting Points</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. AIR SPRING</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. LOWER AIR SPRING MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. TAPERED LEAF SPRING</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. AIR SPRING UPPER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f0301218" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg03/G0301218.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                             scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 17. Air Spring Removal</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. AIR SPRING</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. AIR SPRING MOUNTING HOLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. LOWER SHOCK ABSORBER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. TAPERED LEAF SPRING</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. AXLE SEAT</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>A jack must never be used alone to support vehicle while under-chassis service is being
                            performed. The jack may lower and serious personal injury could result. Always support
                            vehicle with floor stands.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Exhaust air from vehicle and suspension system. Exhaust air by:</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Even if air spring has a leak and is deflated, the air must still be exhausted from
                            system.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Automatic control - height control valve - disconnect link at lower connection, then
                        rotate control arm to exhaust (approximately 45 degrees down) position.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Disconnect air supply line from air spring.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Exhaust air from reservoir.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove air spring assembly.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install replacement air spring assembly and tighten fasteners to specified torque
                    values. Refer to the
                    <hotlnk document="s03012_24.xml" xrefid="x0301202">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect air line to air spring and install height control valve linkage at lower end.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Build vehicle system air pressure to governor cutout pressure and use soap solution to
                    check for leaks.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check for proper ride height adjustment. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s03012_X0301201.xml" xrefid="x0301201">RIDE HEIGHT ADJUSTMENT</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
